sec.p:
A monitoring network of infrared cameras has been created for Hebei Wulingshan Nature Reserve from September 2015 to December 2015; and from March 2016 to June 2018. A sampling effort of 22,379 camera-days across 56 sample sites was achieved (Fig. S1 in 
  Appendix I). A total of 1,736 records for 15 species were obtained. We defined detection at a sample point as one individual photographed during a 30 min period. If more than one individual were identified on a single photograph, we considered this one detection. All detections were summed for each camera site (
  Jia et al., 2014; 
  Li et al., 2010, 
  2014; 
  Liu et al., 2013; 
  Zhang et al., 2012). Then, species were identified using several books (
  Jiang et al., 2015; 
  MacKinnon, Phillipps & He, 2000; 
  Smith & Xie, 2009; 
  Zheng, 2011) and databases (Animal Diversity Web, 
  http://animaldiversity.org/).
